If you are unabel to access the camera and the frames are read as none, this could be a permissions issue which can be solved by adding the user to the videos group:

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/59371075/opencv-error-cant-open-camera-through-video-capture

USing Camorama to test droidcam installed on my phone and linux machine as cheese wont work for me.

To install droidcam i had to sign for it with a public and private key https://ubuntu.com/blog/how-to-sign-things-for-secure-boot

